  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function foreign_new_for_display(display: <link xref="GdkX11.X11Display">GdkX11.X11Display</link>, window: <link href="../xlib-2.0/xlib.Window.html">xlib.Window</link>): <link href="../Gdk-3.0/Gdk.Window.html">Gdk.Window</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for gdk_x11_window_foreign_new_for_display()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Wraps a native window in a <link href="../Gdk-3.0/Gdk.Window.html">Gdk.Window</link>. The function will try to
look up the window using <link xref="GdkX11.X11Window.lookup_for_display"/> first.
If it does not find it there, it will create a new window.</p>  <p>This may fail if the window has been destroyed. If the window
was already known to GDK, a new reference to the existing
<link href="../Gdk-3.0/Gdk.Window.html">Gdk.Window</link> is returned.</p>
  <p>Since 2.24</p>
